The '''Red Moon Saloon''' was a cantina on [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].

It was the site of a meeting between a group of [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] and a [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] named [[Tal Pak]] and his henchman [[Vassk]]. The Rebels were looking for a supply of parts for the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet's]] [[Starship/Legends|starships]]. After negotiating a deal, Pak revealed the location of the parts was the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] training facility on [[Sirpar/Legends|Sirpar]]. Before he could leave with his [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]], Vassk double-crossed him and the Rebels. The henchman planned to turn them all over to the Empire for a bounty. The Rebels managed to defeat the [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] who responded and fled the scene.<ref name="AJ2" />

An incident occurred at the cantina in [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], which involved seven barrels of [[Zelosian wine]], the [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] brothers [[Thok (Gamorrean guard)/Legends|Thok]] and [[Gorc]], a [[Kloo horn/Legends|Kloo horn]], three [[Gungan/Legends|Gungan]] patrons who had been bludgeoned to death, and five fricasseed [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaught]] patrons. This also resulted in the arrest and separation of the two brothers by the Imperial [[Prophets of the Dark Side|Prophetess]] [[Sariss]], resulting in Thok being placed in [[Prefect/Legends|Prefect]] [[Orun Depp]]'s prisons and Gorc being made into a sithspawn after the former squealed about the latter's Force-sensitivity.

